<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Volsce" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Volsce,</orth> (O. Edd. <emph>Volce</emph>), one of the Volsci, a Latin people, often at war with Rome: <bibl n="shak. cor 1.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.10.5" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 10, 5</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.228" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 1, 228</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>Volscies</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.228" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 1, 228</bibl> 253 etc.
